http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/bangalore/Conman-held/article14006911.ece

The Ashoknagar police have arrested a conman who was posing as a CBI officer and threatening government officials and demanding money. The accused, Syed Mohammed Abbas, was trapped based on a complaint. Abbas used to call officials of CPWD and other departments, introduce himself as CBI inspector Syed Hashim, say that a complaint has been filed against them under the Prevention of Corruption Act and demand money to close the case. The police are investigating to ascertain his background.